Natural gas is published in million cubic m3 of natural gas equivalent
column2: i.e. standard air pressure of 101.325 kPa and temperature of 0 degrees Celsius with a lower combustion value of 31.65 (MJ/m3). This unit is also known as the Groningen equivalent.

column1: Gaseous substance of natural origin mainly consisting of methane. This results from the same process that leads to the formation of crude oil. Natural gas is liquefied for transport over long distances by ship.
The gas is liquefied through cooling till about minus 160 degrees Celsius. This makes transport in ships over long distances possible.
The amount of natural gas primarily available for consumption in the Netherlands.
The amount of natural gas delivered to consumers in the Netherlands.
Extraction of natural gas from nature
column2: on-shore and off-shore (in the Dutch territorial part of the North Sea).

column1: Natural gas from other energy commodities transformation
column2: e.g. natural gas production from refinery gas or natural gas production from biogas. Also known as biomethane.

column1: Stock change consists largely of stock changes of liquefied natural gas (Lng). Includes also small changes in the emergency supply of natural gas and in the natural gas pipelines. During extremely cold weather the emergency supply is used to keep the natural gas supply at the normal level. During hot weather the emergency supply is supplemented again. Change in stock is calculated as the opening stock minus the closing stock
column2: in accordance with international energy statistics guidelines. A positive figure means that the stock has decreased
column3: and the supply of natural gas has thus increased. A negative figure means the opposite: an increase in stock and decrease in consumption.

column1: Delivery of fuels for international shipping and aviation
column2: i.e. ships and aircraft departing from Dutch (air)ports and arriving in foreign (air)ports. Bunkers are considered as a form of export and are not included in energy available for consumption in the Netherlands.

column1: . : data not available or not reliable or confidential
In this table an empty cell is also used for cells with value nill.
